cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper deals with the privacy and security aspects of deep neural networks, specifically measuring the amount of sensitive information memorized in each layer of a DNN and protecting the most sensitive layers against potential attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional layers, indicating that it could be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of Trusted Execution Environment (TEE), which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
